narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: How to write a good lab report and structure a lab

Fundamental laboratory techniques used in biological research. A great background in composing scientific literature and communicating raw scientific data to an audience. Knowledge of model organisms used in biological research with applications to various fields like energy, gene therapy, and sustainability.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: Structured assignments and challenging labs. Strengths: The professor. WeaknesS: Sometimes the lab reports can be long and confusing at first but make sure to email your TA regularly.
Strength - excellent professor, excellent TA, she really cares about getting people to learn and prepare for real science

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: Yes its a good lab, not too difficult, lab reports can be demanding but better than all other labs because Moreno cares about you
Absolutely. This is for you if you have little background in lab experience or would like a biology lab credit course.
Yes. It is an intensive course but you'll leave feeling much more comfortable with writing lab reports in the future.
Yes - she actually makes sure you learn instead of filling out pointless reports
